=== Touch Screen ===
This tablet uses GSL1680 from Silead, firmware needs to be loaded, however I haven't got it to work yet. But gslx680-ts-acpi driver works.

=== Wi-Fi ===
Same problem as pine-dontbeevil, Wi-Fi scans just fine, however sometimes it doesn't connect.
https://wiki.postmarketos.org/wiki/Pine_Don%27t_be_evil_devkit_(pine-dontbeevil)#WiFi.2FBluetooth

=== Bluetooth ===
Bluetooth firmware for RTL8723BS loads and working fine.

=== Sixaxis/Accelerometer ===
Bosch BMC150 is in torvalds mainline, but on load, it'll report Invalid chip.

=== Light Sensor ===
Capella CM3218 is the light sensor on this tablet, [https://lwn.net/Articles/557810 there is a patch made by the company itself in mailing list], but doesn't made it's way to mainline.

=== Camera ===
According to danielotero, OV2680 is used in the tablet, but this has not investigated yet. There's currently no patch adding support for this.

=== GPU ===
Uses Intel i915, working out of the box.

=== TF Card Slot ===
Via sdhci_acpi, but it only works sometimes, most of the time it doesn't work.

=== Battery/Charging ===
The power circuit is X-Powers AXP288, this is in torvalds mainline and working just fine.

=== USB Ports (Type-C/Micro) ===
Uses [https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/v4.18/driver-api/usb/dwc3.html Designware Core USB 3.0 Controller], in torvalds mainline and working fine. 

== How to enter flash mode ==

=== DNX Fastboot ===
* Power on the system, wait until the Chuwi logo appears.
* Press Vol Up + Down at the same time.

=== Android Fastboot ===
* Power on the system
* Wait until multiboot screen appears, then click to Android.
* As soon you click "OK", hold down the Vol Down key until the display shows the Android mascot laying down open.

